<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="distribution">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Bolivian endemic restricted to dry forest between 750 and 1200 m in the inter-Andean valleys north of Apolo in the Madidi National Park.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">BOLIVIA. La Paz</emphasis>
: Prov. Tamayo, 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Río">Rio</normalizedToken>
Machariapo, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. Gentry</emphasis>
71078 (MO); Hac. 
<normalizedToken originalValue="Ubitó">Ubito</normalizedToken>
, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">M. Kessler</emphasis>
4007 (LPB); Asariamas, 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">L. Cayola</emphasis>
1746 (LPB); 
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">A. Fuentes</emphasis>
18492 (LPB, MO).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="1" type="notes">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="1">
Very similar to 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Convolvulaceae" genus="Ipomoea" kingdom="Plantae" order="Solanales" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="schulziana">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="1">Ipomoea schulziana</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in habit, leaves and tendency of inflorescence to become paniculate but distinguished by the suburceolate corollas of a distinct fuchsia colour, the limb reduced to five very short lobes.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
